---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="services -- alexander campos" description="AI automation, agentic SEO, cost optimization, and full online presence builds for small businesses.">
  <article>
    <h1>Services</h1>

    <p>
      I help businesses show up where it matters — to people and to the agents
      that increasingly find things for them. Most of this work pays for itself
      within a month.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <div class="services">

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>Full Online Presence Build</h2>
        <p>
          Website, scheduling, calendar integration, contact forms, SEO baseline,
          and the automations that keep it running without you. One build, everything
          connected. Designed for small businesses that don't have a "tech person."
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>Agentic SEO & AI Discoverability</h2>
        <p>
          Search traffic is increasingly driven by agents, not people typing keywords.
          Structured data, machine-readable profiles, agent discovery endpoints — the
          layer that makes your business findable by the tools people actually use now.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>AI Cost Optimization</h2>
        <p>
          If you're running AI and watching the API bill climb — model routing
          and tiered dispatch typically cut 40-60% off spend. Same outputs,
          less money. Audit included.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>Custom AI Automation</h2>
        <p>
          You describe the manual process. I build the pipeline — agent orchestration,
          scheduling, monitoring, whatever it takes to remove you from the loop.
          Processing pipelines, reporting, intake flows.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>Claude Code & MCP Setup</h2>
        <p>
          Your team just got Claude. Now what? Custom MCP servers, persistent
          memory across sessions, team-wide configurations, hooks. The setup
          that makes it actually useful instead of a chatbot with a terminal.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

    </div>

    <hr />

    <p class="pricing">
      Most engagements start with a 30-minute call. Pricing depends on scope.
    </p>

    <p class="contact-alt">
      Prefer email? <a href="mailto:adc.acampos@gmail.com">adc.acampos@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>

  <script is:inline src="/islands/cal-embed.js"></script>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c the infrastructure is the product. ',
      'color: #E8DCC8; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .services {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .service-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--white-08);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .service-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--gold-accent);
  }

  .service-card h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .service-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--white-60);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--gold-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--gold-accent);
    cursor: pointer;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .cta:hover {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
    border-bottom-color: var(--glow-hot);
  }

  .pricing {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .contact-alt {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--white-30);
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
